

# Subject: imperative, ~50–72 characters. Use a type prefix, e.g. feat|fix|docs|refactor|chore|test:
# (Write on line 1 above. Lines starting with # are removed from the final commit.)

# Body (optional): what changed and why; wrap at ~72 columns.
# (Leave one blank line after the subject, then write the body above this comment block.)

# Issue tracking — add one line after the body (that line must NOT start with #):
#   Refs: #123              link to GitHub issue only
#   Fixes: #123             closes issue when merged to the default branch
#   Closes: #123            same as Fixes
#   See also: #123 #124

# Remove anything you don’t need before committing; unused # lines are stripped automatically.
